Despite the uncertainty that may be rocking her marriage to actor Yul Edochie, May Yul Edochie seems to be unworried. Since her husband announced the birth of a child with a colleague, Judy Austin, and his decision to marry her, certain people fear that it would unsettle May who has been married to Yul for years. In a video shared on Instagram a few days ago, May danced to a praise and worship song with positive energy and excitement. Wearing a beautiful blue dress, she also sang along.   Faze, Konga, others thrill at Ruggedman’s Foundation night     Adaorah shines at BET awards     Paul & CeeCee Oniya’s group release Yoruba is my…   May also expressed gratitude to God for being the mouth that speaks for her and the hand that fights for her. “My next post is big, so let’s appreciate God first before I tell you all what it is. This is how the song Onu n’ekwurum by @nkeoma_ started. The mouth that speaks for me, the hand that fights for me…that is my God. My joy cannot be complete without appreciating all my online family members for their endless love, support, and prayers. God bless you all for me,” she wrote.